description:
Integrate the `TaskFileWatcher` with the MeshCore agent registration lifecycle and server startup sequence.

## Server startup wiring

In `apps/server/src/index.ts`, after creating the `TaskStore` and `TaskSchedulerService`, create the `TaskFileWatcher` and `TaskReconciler`, then wire them up:

```typescript
import { TaskFileWatcher } from './services/tasks/task-file-watcher.js';
import { TaskReconciler } from './services/tasks/task-reconciler.js';
import { ensureDamon } from './services/tasks/ensure-damon.js';
import { ensureDefaultTemplates } from './services/tasks/task-templates.js';

// After creating taskStore and taskScheduler:

const onTaskChange = (taskId: string) => {
  // Re-register cron for the changed task
  const task = taskStore.getBySlug(taskId);
  if (task) {
    taskScheduler.registerTask(task);
  } else {
    taskScheduler.unregisterTask(taskId);
  }
};

const taskFileWatcher = new TaskFileWatcher(taskStore, onTaskChange, dorkHome);
const taskReconciler = new TaskReconciler(taskStore, meshCore, dorkHome, onTaskChange);

// Startup sequence:
await ensureDamon(meshCore, dorkHome);
await ensureDefaultTemplates(dorkHome);

// Start global watcher (Damon's tasks directory)
taskFileWatcher.watch(path.join(dorkHome, 'tasks'), 'global');

// Start watchers for all currently registered agents
for (const agent of meshCore.list()) {
  if (agent.projectPath && !agent.isSystem) {
    const tasksDir = path.join(agent.projectPath, '.dork', 'tasks');
    taskFileWatcher.watch(tasksDir, 'project', agent.projectPath);
  }
}

// Start reconciler
taskReconciler.start();
```

## MeshCore lifecycle hooks

Hook into MeshCore's agent registration and unregistration events to start/stop watchers dynamically:

```typescript
// When an agent is registered:
meshCore.on('agent:registered', (agent) => {
  if (agent.projectPath && !agent.isSystem) {
    const tasksDir = path.join(agent.projectPath, '.dork', 'tasks');
    taskFileWatcher.watch(tasksDir, 'project', agent.projectPath);
  }
});

// When an agent is unregistered:
meshCore.on('agent:unregistered', async (agent) => {
  if (agent.projectPath) {
    const tasksDir = path.join(agent.projectPath, '.dork', 'tasks');
    await taskFileWatcher.stopWatching(tasksDir);
  }
});
```

If MeshCore doesn't currently emit events for registration/unregistration, add callback hooks or an event pattern. Check the existing MeshCore implementation and either:
- Use existing event emitter if present
- Add `onRegister` / `onUnregister` callback options
- Or hook into the route handlers that call `meshCore.register()` / `meshCore.unregister()`

## Shutdown cleanup

In the server shutdown handler (SIGTERM, SIGINT), stop all watchers and the reconciler:

```typescript
process.on('SIGTERM', async () => {
  await taskFileWatcher.stopAll();
  taskReconciler.stop();
  // ... existing shutdown logic ...
});
```

## Pass dependencies to routes

Update the `createTasksRouter()` call to pass the `TaskFileWatcher`, `TaskFileWriter`, and `dorkHome` as dependencies so the route handlers can write files:

```typescript
app.use('/api/tasks', createTasksRouter({
  store: taskStore,
  scheduler: taskScheduler,
  meshCore,
  dorkHome,
}));
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- Global watcher starts on server boot watching `{dorkHome}/tasks/`
- Per-agent watchers start for each registered agent's `.dork/tasks/` directory
- New agent registrations trigger new watchers
- Agent unregistrations stop the corresponding watcher
- Reconciler starts on boot with 5-minute interval
- Shutdown cleans up all watchers and stops the reconciler
- Route handlers have access to file-writing infrastructure
- `onTaskChange` callback re-registers cron jobs when tasks change
